      "comment": "STOMPER ROMPER (8) eye-catching debut run after settling well back but winding up strongly into the frame when second (30.30) at this track over 520m. Should be much improved and rates a winning chance. MR. ALEXANDER (4) is a solid beginner and with a good start can clear the draw. Latest effort finished 3rd over 520m at this track beaten 13 lengths (30.54) behind Zipping Kayli in a Maiden on February 19. Rates a key chance on best figures. DOLLAR KEEPING (6) is a handily bred pup making his debut without a trial. Expected to play a major role. BANK KEEPING (3) is a Todd Barnes-trained newcomer by Aston Rupee out of Tania Keeping. Can sneak into the frame at his first appearance.",
